He feels no need to speak at the moment. Neither out of politeness or necessity. His eyes roam over the walls and decorations of past victories Minru's league has seen. Echoes of their footsteps mingle with sounds of the residence, creating a soft, grim mealody to Morcrin's ears. <br>
<br>
Soon the warmth of a fire fills the guesthall and Morcrin removes the soaked, black cloth to let it dry. Grey, slightly worn traveling leathers cover his muscular form. His young, sharp features seem slightly at odd with his long, straight hair that has turned prematurely grey. As if his soul had aged while his body had not. He politley shakes his head &quot;No&quot; to the offerings of food and sweets.<br>
<br>
The man with half a soul, speaks casually as he leans against the wall by the fireplace. His grey eyes reflecting the fire as he watches the flames yet talks to Minru.<br>
&quot;I have not come to leave you with news, my lady.&quot; Morcrin says, his voice serious and blending with the sound of fire and wood popping under the heat.<br>
&quot;Rather...I have come with hope that you may be able to enlighten me.&quot; He stops leaning against the wall and faces Minru, taking a few steps towards her then stops a polite distance away. His hands together as if in deep thought. His piercing eyes on the dark elf.<br>
<br>
&quot;My name is Morcrin.&quot; he says simply. &quot; I am wondering about a man...who, as I understand it.....you knew.&quot;<br>
<br>
For a brief moment, there is only the sound of the fire.<br>
<br>
&quot;A man who was a leader of people and monsters.&quot; The man with half a soul takes one step forward then stops again. &quot; A man named Gray Hateborn.&quot;<br>
<br>
