<br>
The weight of Morcrin’s stare finally brought her out of her trance.  She hesitated, trying to choose her words carefully.  “Lord Regent Gray Hateborn, interesting.  I am not sure how much I can tell you that you have not already heard.  The tales of him have spread far and wide.  One more far-fetched than the next.  No doubt you already know that he once led this very League, or you would not have come here.”<br>
<br>
She spoke as one does when simply reciting facts memorized from a book, not from personal knowledge.  “Lord Regent Gray Hateborn, a human priest of Innoruuk, was raised as a boy in the Overthere after the death of his parents.  This, I know to be true.”  She paused again, took a sip of milk, and bit the head off of a barbarian shaped cookie.  “There are few other things about him where I have been able to sort out the fact from the fiction in the stories.  He was reputed as a ladies man, and I have heard that he had multiple wives.  I have heard strange stories of vampirism.  I do not know whether there is truth in these tales or not.”<br>
<br>
