Morcrin looks at Minru, quietly for a moment. Watching her. Looking at her and as if &quot;through&quot; her. He notices her beautiful features and form as any man would but only lets it distract him for the briefest of moments. He did not travel here to play. Morcrin was a serious man, not a boy just learning about girls. Rather, he looks at her and judges her inner strength through her eyes. He always wanted to know a person's strengths and weak points. The better to kill them if it proved necessary. He did not know if he would need to kill Minru. He felt it would be a shame if he had to. That would not stop him though.<br>
<br>
&quot;I cast a spell to find a soul, a strong soul..the soul of a leader. To see if the mask can bring the soul back into a new form. I believe your brother is dead, Minru. I want to bring him back.&quot;<br>
Morcrin was quiet for a moment. &quot;Unfortunately...there are three other Necromancers who know of the mask....and want your brother's soul for their own ends. Three unusual...people. I met them on my travels and escaped from them. If your brother is truly dead but not gone from this world, they might, just might, have the wit and creativity to actually pull his soul to them and enslave him.&quot; Morcrin continued to explain in his patient voice. &quot; They are building a body, a golem of earth and bone, to host Gray's soul...as a slave. I do not know if they can truly do this. I know that they will try. If Gray truly is dead, they may attempt to find any physical remains left of his original body. The better to bring his soul to them.&quot; Morcrin finished speaking and sat quietly, calmly. Watching Minru.<br>
