<br>
&quot;Where would Gray go if he wanted to be alone?&quot;  She repeated the question quietly to herself.  Minru sighed, and wished she knew.  She wished to know so many things about her brother.  The brother she never had.  What was his favorite color?  What was his favorite food and drink?  What was his life like after their parents died?  Was he treated well in the Overthere?  Was he forced to be a servant like she was?  Were all of the stories she heard about him true?  <br>
<br>
She looked at Morcrin and shrugged.  Very patiently, she begain to explain the situation yet again, &quot;I do not know where Gray spent his time.  We were separated at a very young age.  As for our parents, they are long since dead.  I was never told the manner of their death, if that is what you ask.  All I know is that it was sudden.&quot;<br>
<br>
She sat back in her chair, trying to judge the lack of reaction on Morcrin's face.  Why did he stand there like a rock?  Just what did this fellow have up his sleeve?  And, why in the world did he come here to talk to her?  She smirked slightly, wondering if he was becoming annoyed with her lack of ability to answer his questions and toyed with the idea of making up a story to satisfy his curiousity.  But, what would she say?<br>
<br>
&quot;I fear there is little I am able to tell you regarding your first two questions.  Perhaps I can be of further assistance on the third?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=odyessy7>Odyessy7</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/11/03 1:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1208.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dreams in the Dark</span><hr size=1> &quot;.....I see.&quot; said the man with half a soul. He walked away from the fireplace and towards a window and looked outside. his eyes scanned the horizon through the window. Watching the storm fade away like spent smoke. the sound of rain grew distant and finally, quiet. Morcrin would go over her words in his head later. He would find some way to grab Gray's soul. there was always a way. Just a matter of finding out &quot;How&quot;.<br>
<br>
