<br>
Gaining the blood of another was typically a somewhat simple matter if small amounts were needed.  Small accidents usually proved the best source of collection.  Just a little bit of the right type of poison and a tiny wound would yield a decent sample.  She did not put it past Morcrin to try this on her, as she had done to countless others.  No, better to try to make an arrangement where she would cooperate while gaining his blood in return.<br>
<br>
She let out a laugh.  &quot;My blood you say?  I do not know how my blood will assist in the matter regarding my brother with whom I share no blood ties.  However, I am always needing new blood for my experiments, so I shall make you a deal if you wish.  An exchange as it were... my blood for yours, in equal amounts, at the same time.  What do you say?&quot;<br>
<br>
She pulled a dagger and a vial out of her robe and waited for his response. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=odyessy7>Odyessy7</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 76<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/22/03 2:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1208.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dreams in the Dark</span><hr size=1> The Necromancer admitted to himself he was surprised. He did not expect her to comply. He thought she was clever and now he knew. <br>
<br>
Morcrin knew the risk of giving her his own blood. His essence could be used in any number of ways. He needed the information her blood could give him though, should the spell work. He thought for a moment, looking at her. What was she planning?<br>
<br>
Morcrin drew his own dagger to draw his blood, not trusting Minru's blade. The weapon could be poisoned for all he knew. Carefully, he cut his arm and let his blood drip into the vial he held; the vial he originally intended for the dark elf's blood. As he watched his essence fill the glass container, his mind began to form a plan. He knew how he would use Minru's blood to help him capture Grey's soul. He also knew he could use Minru's blood to send her a little...surprise. She may become a threat to him in the future. He would take care of that.<br>
<br>
